<p><ol>Spot guide for Cape Kiwanda</ol></p>
<p><ul>Accessibility: You can literally drive your vehicle on the beach. Parking fills up before noon on a nice weekend and the beach is sprawling with pickup trucks and Dorry boats launching directly onto the sand near the cape.  </ul></p>
<p><ul>Vibe: Some localism exists. A beginner can expect to be dropped in upon on a crowded day.</ul></p>
<p><ul>Crowd Factor: Medium level crowds, can get busy.</ul></p>
<p><ul>Skill Level: Although a beach break, this spot is best for intermediate level surfers and beyond. Often a dredging shorebreak style wave can be found south from the cape, whereas a reef-pointbreak works on a big swell next to the cape.  </ul></p>

